I'll try to go there again on Saturday. The weather isn't great right now, but it's only Monday.
The difficulties are already starting to appear. I'll probably have A LOT of trouble getting a medical certificate, due to the FAA's stance on certain medications.
Not impossible, but it will take ENORMOUSLY amount of time and require A LOT of extra work.
Even though it's discouraging, it's just another problem to solve and, for now, it seems *completely* manageable to me. It's just that it will take a lot of time and $$.
In case the challenge I'm facing interests you.
The FAA isn't a fan of ADHD. It doesn't issue a medical certificate if you're undergoing treatment for it.
